column5: The NARDA Group is hosting their 12th Annual Wing Night at Birch Dale Lodge on Eagle Lake 9/9/12 @ 7pm. If you are in the area stop in and have some wings and say hi.

I wish we had booked our trip for 2 weeks later! Your wing night sounds like a great way to start a trip on Eagle. I can tell from the posts from Oxdrift that he is really getting excited about going. Tell Ernie I said hi I don't know if he will remember me but I will bet he would remember my ex wife who could speak German with him we went up there from 1996 until 1998
I'll be there....wait I'm always there!!
I'm sure he will remember you and I will be sure to tell him you said hi. And yes you should have come up 2 weeks later!!!!

Dang it. . . . I don't get to that neck of the woods until six days later. Any chance you have delivery service on take out orders?Have a great week in God's garden. Don't go flying through Vermilion Bay on plane throwing a big enough wake to swamp V-Bay Gord's docks!!
